annotation.TEXT: Oh, man. A puzzle room with a reset pipe in the clouds? Sure, that's definitely perfectly normal.
Careful! I wouldn't want to slip and fall to my doom!
That's a miss. I need a better angle than that.
Ooh, a cape feather. I should be able to get that in a moment.
I wonder why the screen scrolls up in this room anyway... I don't think the vertical scrolling was needed here...
Okay, so now we've got really bright lightning flashes, and rising and falling flood waters, within the clouds themselves. Sure, why not?
I guess I'll take the low road first, and then double back for the upper route.
Oh, right. I'd better be careful, since I ended the previous episode without any power ups.
And now, I'm done with this level.
I don't know why, but I want this guy's shell, so I've gotta wait for him to be in the right position...
It's another high/low split. I guess I'll start up here by thwacking some weeds.
In the meantime, let's play like an idiot for a moment.
The next level is a big dot. Hmm... Do I have time for it? Yeah, sure. Why not? I'll play Soft Skies 3 now.
I'm kind of surprised that there's no boss, but whatever. (SMB3's 5-Tower didn't have a boss either.)
Wow, how do I get past all these obstacles unscathed?
Oh, man. I hope I can successfully dodge everything here...
Whoa, that was a bit risky.
So, what has the voting decided? Well, let me open up my usual Notepad file that I use to tally the votes and find out...
Whoa! What did I just say about not slipping and falling to my doom?
Hmm... I think I'm going to need a P-switch.
Ooh, a roulette item! And since I already have a flower and a feather, I know what I'm getting!
Nuts. I don't think I can KO that Chuck. (Maybe if I had a cape, I could try dive bombing...)
I guess I'll keep heading the normal way and play Sky Fortress next.

Alright, so it looks like two levels remain in world 3: #3 Sky Castle, and Sky Secret 2. Now, I suppose you guys can vote if you want, but I'm almost certainly going to be playing both of these levels to finish up world 3 next time, so your votes would only affect which order I do these two levels. So, until next time, folks.
Oh, no. A bridge-building segment? Dang, you, SMB3's 7-5 for starting this trend... (Well, maybe the trend started elsewhere, but SMB3's 7-5 definitely made you build some bridges.)
Once you're up here where more enemies appear, it's impossible to drop back down, so the cape is no longer necessary to proceed.
This room, on the other hand, kind of needs the vertical scrolling, since it's a vertical room!
Looks like this place is starting to get tricky...
I knew I should've worn shin guards for this cloudy expedition...
Forget those three coins. They're not worth it.
Shut up, clock. I'm nearly done here.
Whoa, how did I not become a pancake there?
And, yeah, it's storming out here. But, I guess it's perfectly normal for a plumber to go cloud-swimming during a thunderstorm.
Oh, wait. Can't forget the last Yoshi coin! Almost had a brain fart there!
Aw, not nearly enough enemies to get a 1-up combo with...
And now to make my way back while holding Up, Left, Y, and B almost the whole way.
Did that dive bomb get him? Yeah, looks like it.
Oh, I think I might just be able to get a cape here...
BGM: Super Mario All-Stars - Invincibility Star
Can't you guys hold your baseball practice in a more reasonable place?
Nuts. Just slightly too low.
Well, so much for that guy's shell...
Geez, guys. This isn't a very good place for football practice either.
To be continued...
I'm done with this level's Yoshi coins.
Of course, I gotta check every pipe...
Alright, so Soft Skies 2 won this time! Here we go!
If I ever play Pok√©mon Ruby again, maybe I'll use that nickname.
Yeah, I'm aware of the hidden block here, but I wanted to be fancy in getting that Yoshi coin.
Now, for whatever reason, the game requires you to fly here, for both a Yoshi coin and to progress with the level. Good thing it gives you a feather and doesn't give you a way to hurt yourself here!
I love it when my Zigzagoons bring me Nuggets and Rare Candies.
Yep, just testing the reset pipe.

I think the only way you could make this part unwinnable is if you switched to a flower after picking up the cape, then released the cape without collecting it. Or, getting here with two flowers and releasing/collecting them and the cape in such a way that you overwrite the cape. But, who would be that dumb?
And then I nearly get bitten by that red koopa just as I say that!
Oh, come on! I know it's possible to hit that block!
Definitely reminds me of SMB3's World 5-Tower.
Oh, man. These footballs might make approaching tricky.
Hello, and welcome back to Bowser Rampages Again! Last time, I asked you guys to vote on whether I play Soft Skies 2 or Sky Secret 2 next.
Bah. I was hoping to get at least 40 there so that I'd get a bonus game. I guess that'll have to wait until next time!
Star power, activate!
Geez, and these guys apparently love playing sports in stormy clouds, too! I guess they enjoy livin' on the edge!
Hey, Chuck! Quit dodgin' my fireballs!
I guess there's nothing of interest up there, but I had to be sure, since the game did give me a cape, and there's all this open space past the goal sphere...
BGM: Blaster Master - Area 1
There's that Bramble Blast music (Stickerbrush Symphony) again. Also, is it just me, or are we likely to be in for some nasty weather here?
Waterfalls? Coming from pipes in the clouds? With fish swimming in them? Yeah, sure. I guess that's perfectly normal.
Aha! There we go!
Not like that, apparently...
